as \u201Cerror\u201D or \u201Cfail\u201D\u2014these typically indicate issues: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/7/760ac3cf30b7e3c265ed1a0aaf0d9585d4dfc864.png]\nDescription: The image displays a log output related to the IdentityServer4 framework, specifically from the TokenValidator. The log entries are timestamped with the date and time \u00222025-03-25 15:17:08.\u0022 A prominent message indicates a failure with \u0022Invalid reference token\u0022 alongside the label \u0022[ERROR].\u0022 The structured log entries detail parameters such as \u0022ValidateLifetime\u0022: true, \u0022AccessTokenType\u0022: \u0022Reference\u0022, \u0022ExpectedScope\u0022: \u0022IdentityServerApi\u0022, and \u0022TokenHandle\u0022: \u0022430E035D7267C763BAF1963D844EE37A4602937BCB4DDCAF8287F3689B7D65.\u0022 The purpose of the log is to record issues during the validation process of access tokens in IdentityServer4.\n\n\n  \n  3. Transactions  \nDifferent transactions are marked with bracketed numbers. Focus on those that occurred earliest by time, as these might be the root cause of the issue, while later ones could just be consequences. \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/6/6935e767b3d93b7686b0be8ada91185f0ed6bb9c.png]\nDescription: The image displays a log output that captures error messages related to token validation within IdentityServer4 on March 25, 2025. It includes timestamped entries indicating the failure of \u0022Invalid reference token\u0022 associated with the \u0022TokenValidator.\u0022 The visible JSON structures show parameters such as \u0022ValidateLifetime,\u0022 \u0022AccessTokenType,\u0022 \u0022ExpectedScope,\u0022 and \u0022TokenHandle,\u0022 with specific values provided for each. The error occurrences are highlighted with numerical identifiers in brackets [30] and [18], indicating multiple instances of the same error type in the log data. The apparent purpose of this output is to diagnose issues related to authentication and authorization during API calls.\n\n\n  \n  4. Points of failure  \nIdentify the part of the application where the error occurred. This helps in understanding the root cause and guides your next steps: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/5/5d9832e5a961e0b3262630503093cfbc16d94db8.png]\nDescription: The image displays a log entry from a system generated on March 25, 2025, at 15:17:08.609, indicating an error related to IdentityServer4. The log entry includes a JSON-like structure showing properties such as \u0022ValidateLifetime\u0022 set to true, \u0022AccessTokenType\u0022 as \u0022Reference,\u0022 \u0022ExpectedScope\u0022 which is \u0022IdentityServerApi,\u0022 and a \u0022TokenHandle\u0022 with a lengthy alphanumeric string. The purpose of the log is to report an invalid reference token during validation, suggesting issues with access tokens within the IdentityServer4 context.\n\n\n  \n For example, IdentityServer is related to user login, while Origam.DA.Service is connected to the DB Server. \n   Fixing errors \n Once you locate and hopefully understand the source of the problem, you can go to Architect and fix it. This is a broad topic, but we\u2019ll touch on a common example. \n For instance, a frequent error occurs when creating a Data Structure. If you add an Entity and set its AllFields property to False, but forget to include the \u201CId\u201D field manually, it will cause issues in the application\u2014since \u201CId\u201D is required: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/e/e8149f362d1514a6322ec2cea346d4f0100ea383.png]\nDescription: The image displays a modal error notification with the title \u0022Error.\u0022 It contains a message stating, \u0022An error has occured. There may be some details in the log file.\u0022 A red triangle with an exclamation mark is shown as a visual alert beside the text. Below the message, there is a blue button labeled \u0022OK,\u0022 indicating the option to acknowledge the error message. ","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-05-01T23:55:29"},"vector":[-0.025113288,0.004210961,-0.060039062,0.00929141,-0.01101802,-0.03156053,-0.008443766,0.009263633,-0.042159893,0.026398424,-0.0047618737,-0.010252873,0.01154486,0.0046628295,0.014508335,-0.022934621,0.03278143,0.009527971,0.0108577795,0.036439903,-0.022407873,0.011653386,0.03350021,0.007523743,-0.017294904,0.03419491,0.007719029,-0.022930091,0.029518418,0.045634393,0.017169558,-0.051099602,0.003402613,-0.021576835,-0.008595645,0.0012686367,-0.002534479,0.029429147,-0.042704042,0.017208055,-0.02203131,0.015429486,0.011478219,-0.04620863,0.037106432,-0.06982163,0.0120833805,0.0028897084,0.0019429992,-0.026704177,0.002235079,-0.017175617,0.037664283,-0.035700418,0.00072544353,0.015460977,-0.03732323,-0.013159764,-0.03291635,-0.013843279,-0.00578511,-0.009534922,-0.014774828,-0.020118872,0.018695649,0.022032902,-0.011989599,0.00927696,-0.019633327,-0.011221532,0.010695721,0.053563543,-0.037551492,-0.017892275,-0.07928297,0.010355151,0.001406601,0.024153195,-0.031883176,0.05037641,-0.009279782,0.010348976,-0.050003678,0.0020668565,-0.008935581,0.0653235,-0.036003362,0.032610774,0.02712386,0.022405319,-0.031520344,-0.033819545,0.06363078,-0.008936816,0.010578776,0.00015355239,-0.030293787,0.009057491,-0.006470612,-0.00039325075,0.017543659,-0.012371015,-0.04254643,0.0016441994,-0.029188128,-0.0023458079,0.03315101,-0.045498945,-0.017735079,-0.015983926,-0.0009611449,0.017510831,0.04033527,0.022819674,-0.01648047,0.005472642,0.0005556945,-0.027591985,0.0028509477,0.019253792,0.013121385,0.04611276,0.030462882,-0.044066243,-0.0336874,0.027871078,0.0024583116,0.04638135,-0.013608184,0.026631689,-0.009140444,-0.01944563,-0.015423507,-0.006223353,-0.07634766,0.019735899,0.03624799,0.010782071,0.024376763,-0.044275448,0.046409566,-0.008288172,-0.040305763,-0.0